            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Countertop Microwave Ovens</h3>
              <p>
                Countertop microwave ovens are the most common type and are
                generally more affordable and easier to install. However, they
                are also prone to a variety of repair needs. One frequent issue
                is a faulty door switch, which can prevent the microwave from
                heating food. If your microwave isn't working properly, a
                qualified technician may need to replace the door switch. Water
                or insect infestation can also disrupt the electronics,
                requiring a thorough cleaning or replacement of affected
                components. The turntable's turning mechanism can also fail,
                which may necessitate the replacement of the motor or belt.
                Issues with the high voltage diode or capacitor can prevent the
                microwave from powering on, requiring specialized testing and
                repair.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Built-in Microwave Ovens</h3>
              <p>
                Built-in microwave ovens offer a sleek, integrated look but come
                with their own set of challenges. Repairing these units often
                requires more expertise due to their complex installation. A
                broken microwave door can be particularly problematic as it
                usually involves more intricate components compared to
                countertop models. Faulty door switches are still a common
                issue, but accessing them can be more difficult. Control panel
                failures are another frequent problem, often requiring the
                replacement of the entire panel by a qualified technician.
                Additionally, built-in microwaves are more susceptible to
                defective magnetrons, which may need to be replaced if the unit
                stops heating food effectively.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Over-the-Range Microwave Ovens</h3>
