                Over-the-range microwave ovens combine microwave cooking with a
                range hood, making them multifunctional but also more complex to
                repair. They often suffer from the same door switch issues as
                other types but may also experience problems with the
                ventilation system. A defective magnetron or high voltage diode
                can render the microwave useless, necessitating expert advice
                for a proper fix. The control panel can also fail, requiring a
                replacement part to restore functionality. Given their
                placement, these microwaves are also more prone to insect
                infestation, which can affect the electronics and require a
                thorough cleaning and inspection.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
