                high voltage components such as the diode, capacitor, and
                magnetron are often the first to fail due to the high energy
                demands. These microwaves also have more complex door switches
                and control panels that can malfunction. Water or insect
                infestation is a more significant risk in commercial kitchens,
                potentially affecting multiple components and requiring
                extensive cleaning and part replacement. Given the critical role
                these appliances play in food service, prompt and expert repair
                is essential to minimize downtime.
              </p>
            </div>
